  • Constructor Details

    • Album

      protected Album​(java.lang.String name, User owner) throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
      Base constructor for the album. Gives the album a name without adding any pictures. Doesn't allow for two albums owned by the same user to have the same name.
      Parameters:
      name - Name for the album.
      owner - The album's owner.
      Throws:
      java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if an existing album owned by the same user has this name.

    • Album

      public Album​(java.lang.String name, User owner, java.util.List<Picture> pictures) throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
      Constructor for the album that gives it a name and also adds some pictures. Most useful when creating an album from a list of search results.
      Parameters:
      name - Name for the album.
      owner - The album's owner.
      pictures - List of pictures that will be added to this album.
      Throws:
      java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if an existing album owned by the same user has this name.

    • Album

      public Album​(java.lang.String name, java.util.HashSet<Picture> pictures)
      Constructor for the album that gives it a name and also adds some pictures. The album is not tied to a User instance. Most useful when creating an album to represent a list of search results, that may or may not be saved as a new album.
      Parameters:
      name - Name for the album.
      pictures - List of pictures that will be added to this album.
